entry.name: Private Creator ID
entry.definition: - The Private Creator ID for this block of added Private Elements. The value is "A.L.I. Technologies, Inc.".

entry.name: Filename
entry.definition: - Holds the filename of the original SOP Instance.

entry.name: Data Blob of a Visit
entry.definition: - Holds the McKesson Radiology system proprietary database information regarding the ‘visit’ for which the SOP Instance belongs.

entry.name: Revision Number
entry.definition: - The revision number of the extended info image.

entry.name: Unix Timestamp
entry.definition: - The Unix format time-stamp of the creation of the extended info image.

entry.name: Bag ID
entry.definition: - The McKesson Radiology Bag ID associated with an image.

entry.name: Original Study UID
entry.definition: - The original Study UID specified in the SOP Instance

entry.name: Overlay Grayscale Value
entry.definition: - The MONOCHROME2 grayscale value (0 to 255) to use when displaying or printing an overlay for the SOP Instance.

entry.name: Anonymization Status
entry.definition: - Value of "ANONYMIZED" means that the confidential patient information has been removed or replaced in the DICOM header. Note that this does not guarantee that any confidential information ‘burned into’ the pixel data has been removed.

entry.name: Instance Type
entry.definition: - The Instance Type of images created on McKesson Radiology. Possible values:

entry.name: IP Converted Frame
entry.definition: This tag will be used as a marker which will be checked when a DICOM attribute collection of NM images is being processed. It can be added with a value of "IPConvertedFrame" when McKesson Radiology is processing NM images that have multiple frames.
